    <section class="kotlin-overview-section _features">
        <h2 class="section-header">Why Kotlin?</h2>
        <div class="section-content">
            <ul class="kotlin-features-list">
                    <li class="kotlin-feature _concise js-popup-open-button"
                        data-popup-id="kotlin-feature_concise">
                        <div class="feature-image">
                            <div class="feature-icon _concise"></div>
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="feature-title">Concise</h3>
                        <p class="feature-description">Drastically reduce the amount of boilerplate code.</p>
                        <span class="feature-example-link">See example</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="kotlin-feature _safe js-popup-open-button"
                        data-popup-id="kotlin-feature_safe">
                        <div class="feature-image">
                            <div class="feature-icon _safe"></div>
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="feature-title">Safe</h3>
                        <p class="feature-description">Avoid entire classes of errors such as null pointer exceptions.</p>
                        <span class="feature-example-link">See example</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="kotlin-feature _interoperable js-popup-open-button"
                        data-popup-id="kotlin-feature_interoperable">
                        <div class="feature-image">
                            <div class="feature-icon _interoperable"></div>
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="feature-title">Interoperable</h3>
                        <p class="feature-description">Leverage existing libraries for the JVM, Android, and the browser.</p>
                        <span class="feature-example-link">See example</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="kotlin-feature _tool-friendly js-popup-open-button"
                        data-popup-id="kotlin-feature_tool-friendly">
                        <div class="feature-image">
                            <div class="feature-icon _tool-friendly"></div>
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="feature-title">Tool-friendly</h3>
                        <p class="feature-description">Choose any Java IDE or build from the command line.</p>
                        <span class="feature-example-link">See example</span>
                    </li>
            </ul>
        </div>

            <div class="overview-popup overview-popup_concise _hidden js-popup"
                 id="kotlin-feature_concise">
                <div class="popup-content">
                    <h3 id="concise">Concise</h3>
<p>Create a POJO with getters, setters, <code>equals()</code>, <code>hashCode()</code>, <code>toString()</code> and <code>copy()</code> in a single line:</p>
<pre><code class="code _highlighted" data-lang="text/x-kotlin">data class Customer(val name: String, val email: String, val company: String)
</code></pre>
<p>Or filter a list using a lambda expression:</p>
<pre><code class="code _highlighted" data-lang="text/x-kotlin">val positiveNumbers = list.filter { it &gt; 0 }
</code></pre>
<p>Want a singleton? Create an object:</p>
<pre><code class="code _highlighted" data-lang="text/x-kotlin">object ThisIsASingleton {
    val companyName: String = "JetBrains"
}
</code></pre>

                </div>

                <div class="popup-close-button js-popup-close-button"
                     data-popup-id="kotlin-feature_concise"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="overview-popup-overlay"></div>
            <div class="overview-popup overview-popup_safe _hidden js-popup"
                 id="kotlin-feature_safe">
                <div class="popup-content">
                    <h3 id="safe">Safe</h3>
<p>Get rid of those pesky NullPointerExceptions, you know, The Billion Dollar Mistake</p>
<pre><code class="code _highlighted" data-lang="text/x-kotlin">var output: String
output = null   // Compilation error
</code></pre>
<p>Kotlin protects you from mistakenly operating on nullable types</p>
<pre><code class="code _highlighted" data-lang="text/x-kotlin">val name: String? = null    // Nullable type
println(name.length())      // Compilation error
</code></pre>
<p>And if you check a type is right, the compiler will auto-cast it for you</p>
<pre><code class="code _highlighted" data-lang="text/x-kotlin">fun calculateTotal(obj: Any) {
    if (obj is Invoice)
        obj.calculateTotal()
}
</code></pre>

                </div>

                <div class="popup-close-button js-popup-close-button"
                     data-popup-id="kotlin-feature_safe"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="overview-popup-overlay"></div>
            <div class="overview-popup overview-popup_interoperable _hidden js-popup"
                 id="kotlin-feature_interoperable">
                <div class="popup-content">
                    
<h3 id="interoperable">Interoperable</h3>
<p>Use any existing library on the JVM, as there’s 100% compatibility, including SAM support.</p>
<pre><code class="code _highlighted" data-lang="text/x-kotlin">import io.reactivex.Flowable
import io.reactivex.schedulers.Schedulers

Flowable
    .fromCallable {
        Thread.sleep(1000) //  imitate expensive computation
        "Done"
    }
    .subscribeOn(Schedulers.io())
    .observeOn(Schedulers.single())
    .subscribe(::println, Throwable::printStackTrace)
</code></pre>
<p>Target either the JVM or JavaScript. Write code in Kotlin and decide where you want to deploy to</p>
<pre><code class="code _highlighted" data-lang="text/x-kotlin">import kotlin.browser.window

fun onLoad() {
    window.document.body!!.innerHTML += "&lt;br/&gt;Hello, Kotlin!"
}
</code></pre>

                </div>

                <div class="popup-close-button js-popup-close-button"
                     data-popup-id="kotlin-feature_interoperable"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="overview-popup-overlay"></div>
            <div class="overview-popup overview-popup_tool-friendly _hidden js-popup"
                 id="kotlin-feature_tool-friendly">
                <div class="popup-content">
                    <h3 id="tooling">Tooling</h3>
<p>A language needs tooling and at JetBrains, it's what we do best!</p>
<p class="image-block"><img alt="Tooling" src="/assets/images/index/features/tooling/tooling1.png" srcset="/assets/images/index/features/tooling/tooling1%402x.png 2x"/></p>
<p class="image-block"><img alt="Tooling" src="/assets/images/index/features/tooling/tooling2.png" srcset="/assets/images/index/features/tooling/tooling2%402x.png 2x"/></p>

                </div>

                <div class="popup-close-button js-popup-close-button"
                     data-popup-id="kotlin-feature_tool-friendly"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="overview-popup-overlay"></div>

    </section>

<h2 class="overview-header">Try Kotlin</h2>
<section class="kotlin-overview-section _code-examples">
    <div class="kotlin-overview-code-example-tabs">
        <div class="g-layout overview-group">
            <div class="tab is_active js-tab" data-tab-id="kotlin-code-example-simplest">
                <div class="text">Simplest version</div>
            </div>
            <div class="tab js-tab" data-tab-id="kotlin-code-example-object-oriented">
                <div class="tab-text">An Object-oriented Hello</div>
            </div>
            <div class="tab js-tab" data-tab-id="kotlin-code-example-coroutine">
                <div class="tab-text">Coroutines</div>
            </div>
            <a class="tab overview-examples" href="https://play.kotlinlang.org/byExample/overview">
                <div class="tab-text">More examples</div>
                <span class="more-examples-icon"></span>
            </a>

        </div>
        <div class="kotlin-overview-code-example" id="kotlin-code-example-simplest">
            <div theme="darcula" class="sample" auto-indent="true" data-min-compiler-version="1.3">
                package hello

                fun main() {
                println("Hello World")
                }
            </div>

        </div>

        <!-- code example -->
        <div class="kotlin-overview-code-example is_hidden" id="kotlin-code-example-object-oriented">
            <div theme="darcula" class="sample" auto-indent="true" data-min-compiler-version="1.3" args="Kotlin">
                class Greeter(val name: String) {
                fun greet() {
                println("Hello, $name")
                }
                }

                fun main(args: Array&lt;String&gt;) {
                Greeter(args[0]).greet()
                }
            </div>
        </div>
        <!-- code example -->
        <div class="kotlin-overview-code-example is_hidden" id="kotlin-code-example-coroutine">
            <div theme="darcula" class="sample" auto-indent="true" folded-button="false" data-min-compiler-version="1.3">
                import kotlinx.coroutines.*
                //sampleStart
                suspend fun main() = coroutineScope {
                    for (i in 0 until 10) {
                        launch {
                            delay(1000L - i * 10)
                            print("❤️$i ")
                        }
                    }
                }
                //sampleEnd
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
